Since in the first Java program, the output is printed with spaces between each element, but no trailing space. Wait, looking at the first Java code:

for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
    System.out.print(idorder.get(i));
    System.out.print(" ");
}

So that would print all elements followed by a space, including the last one. So the output would be like "2 3 1 " (with a trailing space). But in Java, when you print with print, it doesn't add a newline. So the entire output is the numbers separated by spaces, with a trailing space.
